[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, Google has released a fast mode for V3. And you know what? I\'m just going to let the Yeti tell you. I can\'t believe it. V3\'s fast mode is finally here. It\'s so good and it costs less. This is amazing. So, the question, of course, is'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'does this break the rule of fast, cheap, and good, but you can only pick two. So, today we\'ll dive in for an AB comparison, plus go over the cost of fast mode, which I I think you\'re going'

[00:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to be pleased with. Plus, I\'ve got an interesting VO3 prompt formula and one really big hack that you\'re definitely gonna want to know. So, yeah, without much fanfare and sort of ironically after Google released the V3 API, well,'

[00:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'just about everywhere, uh, they stealth dropped a fast mode. I will say that there\'s not much, you know, technical information out there available on it right now, but I can tell you that it does generate audio and I mean, it does'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'so, as the name implies, quickly. But the real seller here is of course the cost. And we are going to take a look at that in just a second. But first, let\'s see if it\'s worth your time. This morning I did crib up an ode to one of my favorite TV shows, Twin Peaks. Uh'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'let\'s see how Fast Mode does. This town has its secrets, agent. But things like this don\'t happen here. I found the body. It was wrapped in plastic. You'

[01:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'see, this town, it\'s not like other places. The owls aren\'t what they seem. And the coffee, well, it\'s got secrets, too. It is a damn fine cup of Joe. You\'re looking in all the wrong places,'

[01:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'agent. You need to be in the woods talking to the owls. There\'s a cabin out there. A black lodge. Never go in it. Promise me. You\'re going to want to see what\'s on this, agent.'

[01:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'It\'s creepy. [Music] Well, I think I\'ve just solved the case. Do you have any chewing gum? So, yeah,'

[02:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that is pretty good. Uh, to note, all of the clips there were generated in V3 fast, although I did take it through a Topaz upscale. Uh, that\'s just kind of par for the course. So, now let\'s take'

[02:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'an AB look at fast mode versus well, they call it quality. I just call it the big daddy mode. So, kicking off with this Fallout inspired prompt. Uh, let\'s take a look at VO3. Big daddy. Overall, pretty solid output. There is a bit of a'

[02:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'stutter step on our female character here. Or maybe she just tripped on a vine. Uh, to note, I did also prompt for dialogue here. We did not get dialogue. I\'d say there\'s like it\'s usually around like a 25% chance of failure on dialogue'

[02:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'when you prompt for it in VO3. At least that\'s what I\'ve been noticing. And then, you know, like a 25% chance you might get subtitles as well. Now, taking a look at the exact same prompt run in VO3 fast. And I I think you\'re going to'

[02:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'be kind of surprised by this. We need to be careful in here. Could be bandits or worse. Always is. Keep your eyes open. Aside from the obvious thing in which we did get our dialogue this time around,'

[03:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the other sort of really surprising thing was that uh like these two characters across both V3 quality and V3 fast. I mean, they remain pretty consistent down to the fact that both characters have the same vault numbers.'

[03:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'That was something I did not prompt for. Ultimately, I do think the fast model is just the normal model, albeit without like one or two final rendering passes. In terms of prompt accuracy, I mean, the the fast mode does get in pretty much'

[03:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'everything that we asked for from the normal version. Uh, take for example this Bond inspired output. A little something extra for your wrist, Bond. If you need to make a quick exit, and if I don\'t.'

[03:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, obviously quality does look pretty good, although we did get the subtitles there. And it did miss out on the punchline. Here it is in fast. A little something extra for your wrist bond if you need to make a quick exit. And if I'

